3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour based on the 1-hour TWAP premium between the perpetual price and the underlying index. The on-chain nature means all funding rate calculations are transparent and verifiable on Hyperliquid's L1 chain. Funding payments are automatically settled in USDC every hour at the top of the hour, with rates typically ranging from -0.01% to +0.01% per hour."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SEI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SEI represents a promising Layer-1 blockchain focused on DeFi applications, making its perpetual contract attractive for both directional trades and funding rate arbitrage. The mid-tier trading volume provides adequate liquidity while maintaining potential for meaningful funding rate spreads during market volatility."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SEI/USDT funding rates on Hyperliquid have shown typical Layer-1 token behavior with periodic spikes during major announcements or broader L1 narratives. The 1-hour funding intervals create more opportunities for rate capture compared to traditional 8-hour cycles. Historical data shows funding rates often correlate with SEI ecosystem developments and general DeFi sentiment. Peak funding periods typically occur during SEI mainnet updates or major partnership announcements."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The on-chain nature of Hyperliquid creates unique arbitrage opportunities when funding rates diverge significantly from CEX platforms. Traders can capitalize on the 1-hour funding frequency by executing shorter-term strategies that wouldn't be viable on 8-hour platforms. Cross-DEX arbitrage becomes possible by pairing Hyperliquid positions with centralized exchanges offering SEI perpetuals. The no-KYC requirement allows for rapid position adjustments without verification delays."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid's single-chain ecosystem means SEI positions are subject to both SEI price risk and potential Hyperliquid chain issues. The platform's relative newness compared to established CEXs introduces counterparty risk despite the on-chain transparency. USDC-only settlements mean exposure to USDC depeg risk, though this is mitigated by the stablecoin's track record. Liquidity can vary significantly during volatile periods, potentially impacting large position exits."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Hyperliquid's 1-hour funding compare to other exchanges for SEI?","answer":"Hyperliquid's hourly funding provides 8x more frequent settlement opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour cycles on CEXs. This creates more granular arbitrage opportunities and reduces funding rate risk exposure periods."},{"question":"What makes SEI/USDT attractive for funding rate arbitrage on Hyperliquid?","answer":"SEI's mid-tier volume provides adequate liquidity while maintaining funding rate volatility. The Layer-1 narrative creates periodic funding spikes, and Hyperliquid's on-chain transparency allows for better rate prediction."},{"question":"Are there withdrawal limits for SEI positions on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Hyperliquid operates as a non-custodial DEX with no traditional withdrawal limits since funds remain in your wallet. However, large positions may face liquidity constraints during volatile periods."},{"question":"How reliable is funding rate data for SEI on Hyperliquid?","answer":"All funding rate calculations are transparent and verifiable on-chain, providing higher reliability than centralized exchanges. The deterministic nature of blockchain execution ensures consistent rate application every hour."}]}]
